                  No duplicates
                  No order
                  Allows one null
            Set<Integer> set = new HashSet<>();
            🔹 Internal Working-> Uses HashMap internally
                  private transient HashMap<E,Object> map;
                   When you do: set.add(10); Internally:  map.put(10, PRESENT);
            🔹 How Duplicate is Prevented
                  Compute hashCode()
                  Find bucket
                  Compare using equals()
                  If already exists → NOT added
            Internal Flow Example:
                        set.add("A");
                        set.add("B");
                        set.add("A"); // duplicate 
                  Internally:
                        hash(A) → bucket1 → inserted
                        hash(B) → bucket2 → inserted
                        hash(A) → bucket1 → already exists → ignored
            🔹 Structure (Java 8+)
                  Bucket → LinkedList → Red-Black Tree (if large)
            🔹 Time Complexity:
                  Operation	Time
                  add()      	O(1)
                  remove()	O(1)
                  contains()	O(1)

